President Biden has nominated Dr. Philip Jefferson for Vice Chair and Dr. Adriana Kugler as a Member on the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System. Additionally, he plans to renominate Dr. Lisa Cook for an additional full term as a Member. President Biden highlighted the positive economic indicators under his administration, such as job creation, decreasing inflation, and a strong job market. He expressed confidence that these nominees will contribute to the continued economic recovery. Dr. Jefferson, a current member of the Board of Governors, has experience in academia and previously worked at the Federal Reserve. Dr. Cook, also a current member, has a background in economics and international relations. Dr. Kugler, currently serving as the U.S. Executive Director at the World Bank Group, has expertise in labor markets and applied econometrics.